<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><div style=""><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"></font></span></div><span lang="en-GB" style="text-align: start; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" style=""><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">I am writing to update you with regards to our computing strategy this academic year. Last year a number of parents raised concerns about screen time, monitoring of internet access and what we as a school were doing to control this. With this in mind we have altered our approach to technology to ensure that it adds value to the education we provide, whilst minimising the potential ‘threats’ that it can pose to our students.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">In Key Stage 3 (Years 7-9) we will be providing access to Macbooks and other technologies for all lessons, as and when appropriate. &nbsp;We have a number of class Macbook sets that teachers and subjects will use to supplement in-class teaching and learning. All departments also have access to iPads that can be booked out in the same way.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">In addition, we have one dedicated classroom that will serve as a computer suite where all computing lessons will take place. This will primarily be used by our computing teacher, but again, will be made available to subjects, teachers and students as appropriate. We will be adding a 3D printer to the suite and also plan to add additional software/subscriptions in a variety of subject areas.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Our Year 10 students will each receive a Macbook that they will keep for the duration of their IGCSE courses. Many IGCSE courses require students to complete extended research and access online resources; some will also require coursework pieces to be written up and submitted.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">We feel that this technology model will allow us to control the use of technology so that it adds value whilst minimising the ‘negative impacts that too much exposure to technology can cause. If you have any further questions, please do not hesitate to contact me - matt.gilberthorpe@britishschoolyangon.org</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Kind regards,</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Matt Gilberthorpe (BA, M.Ed, NPQH)</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><b>Head of Secondary</b></span></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; margin: 0px;"><br></div></font></span></div></div>]]></td>
</tr>
